U.S. Steel Serbia Sets Up Roll Service With Canadian Partner

-- B y   G o r d a n a   F i l i p o v i c
-- 
2011-05-31T13:36:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/u-s-steel-serbia-sets-up-roll-service-with-canadian-partner.html
The Serbian unit of U.S. Steel opened
a new roll servicing unit at its cold rolling mill plant, part
of a joint venture it runs with the Canadian Court Holdings
Ltd., the company said in an e-mail.  The $5 million facility, operated by the Serbian Roll
Service Company d.o.o., will offer services to other companies
as well, U.S. Steel  Serbia , based in the town of Smederevo, said
in a statement.  “This joint venture currently employs six people, who are
performing chrome plating and roll grinding for the needs of
U.S. Steel Serbia,” a company statement cited General Director
of U.S. Steel Serbia Matthew Perkins as saying. “Our intention
is to make their services available to other companies as
well.”  U.S. Steel’s European operations, which also include a
steel mill in Kosice, Slovakia, operates at “92 percent of raw
steel capability for the first quarter, a 15 percent increase
over the fourth quarter 2010,” Shipments increased by 17
percent to 1.4 million tons due to improved economic conditions.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gordana Filipovic in Belgrade at 
 gfilipovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  